[src:dynamical-systems-math/lyapunov-stability] It has been shown that near to a point of equilibrium which is Lyapunov stable the system remains stable under small disturbances.
[src:dynamical-systems-math/lyapunov-stability] For larger input disturbances the study of such systems is the subject of control theory and applied in control engineering.
[src:dynamical-systems-math/lyapunov-stability] For systems with inputs, one must quantify the effect of inputs on the stability of the system.
